sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36558
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PoPS estrogen receptor beta and ERE operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part is designed to code for the Estrogen Receptor Beta and has a promoter and operon at the end that is designed to arrest transcription of whatever gene follows the promoter at the end of our composite part when estrogen is detected. The parts that make up the composite are the promoter, which is a strong, general E. coli promoter, a medium strength ribosome binding site, the cDNA for estrogen receptor beta, the stop codon, the general terminator which arrests transcription, the strong, general E. coli promoter for the gene that follows ER beta, and the ERE operon that ER beta can bind to to arrest transcription of the gene that follows the ER beta gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ashley Henderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts that make up this composite are as follows and in this order: BBa_J23110 BBa_M36559 BBa_M36560 BBa_M36561 BBa_J23104 BBa_M36562 They come from both the parts registry and are edited basic parts that we manually added to the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In our design we ordered the basic parts into a precise order that would allow the ER beta to be made and able to arrest the transcription of the the gene that follows by binding to the ERE operon.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36559
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a short RBS with a spacer of 6 Bp attached to the end.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Raitor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part uses a RBS in the iGEM registry that did not include a 6 Bp spacer. This part is based on the standard RBS BBa_J34803 found in the iGEM Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The only design considerations we had to take into account was picking a spacer of 6Bp and adding it to the end of BBa_J34803 (an already existing RBS).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36560
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the cDNA Sequence of the human ESR2 (or ER-Beta) gene. It encodes for a protein which responds to estrogen (specifically estradiol) levels in the cells environment.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Raitor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence comes from human DNA, but the sequence used in the part is the cDNA format in oder to avoid the necessity of splicing the mRNA produced before translation (something that prokaryotic cells are not capable of). The cDNA sequence was obtained from the website www.sinobiological.com and the link to the specific page is listed here: http://www.sinobiological.com/ESR2-cDNA-Clone-g-2579.html
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In finding the ESR2 coding sequence, we had to be sure to use the cDNA sequence as that would not need to be cut apart as a full cDNA sequence would. Using the cDNA sequence made our part shorter and increased its versatility, as it could now be used in prokaryotic cells.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36561
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This terminator is a general terminator of transcription. It forms a stem loop which stops transcrip
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This terminator is a general E. coli terminator that forms a 64 base pair stem loop. The structure of the stem loop arrests transcription of a gene. This basic part is to be added at the end of a gene to stop transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ashley Henderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of this part is from the parts registry. It is known as BBa_B0010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The reason we chose this part for our project is that it is a simple terminator and forms one stem loop. Nothing in the sequence was changed from the obtained version from the parts registry.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36562
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Estrogen Response Element- operon that the estrogen receptor beta binds to
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a short sequence that the estrogen receptor beta attaches to after it detects estrogen and forms a homodimer. When bound to this ERE site, the estrogen receptor can activate or deactivate transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ashley Henderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence we used was obtained from this research article. "Cooperative Estrogen Receptor Interaction with Consensus or Variant Estrogen Responsive Elements in Vitro" Carolyn M. Klinge, Franklin V. Peale, Jr., Russell Hilf, et al.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We used the sequence CTG as the "NNN" in the center of the sequence design.
